<h1>Black Beans</h1>
<image src="images/black-beans"></image>
<h2>Description</h2>
<p>These black beans can be used for nachos, burritos, burrito bowls, or just on their own!</p>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
    <li>1 lb dry black beans (2 cups)</li>
    <li>3 cups water</li>
    <li>1 large onion</li>
    <li>6 cloves garlic</li>
    <li>1 tsp oregano</li>
    <li>1 tsp ground cumin</li>
    <li>1 tsp cilantro (OR half bunch fresh)</li>
    <li>2 pinches red pepper flake</li>
    <li>4 tsp sugar</li>
    <li>4 tbsp white wine vinegar</li>
    <li>salt and pepper to taste</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
    <li>Combine all ingredients into an instant pot.</li>
    <li>Set to 35 minutes at pressure.</li>
    <li>After it has been at pressure for 35 minutes, let the instant pot naturally release for 20 minutes.</li>
    <li>Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.</li>
</ol>